evolution.config.animatedTextures.commen: Use animated textures when available in the current resource pack. Disabling will improve performance, but animated textures, such as fire, will appear static.
evolution.config.bodyTemperature.comment: The temperature unit used by body temperature in the game.
evolution.config.celestialEquator.commen: Shows a red line in the skies representing the Celestial Equator.
evolution.config.celestialForceAll.comme: Shows all the debug options on this list, regardless of the individual config of each option.
evolution.config.celestialPoles.comment: Shows two dots in the skies, the red one represents the Celestial North Pole, while the blue one represents the Celestial South Pole.
evolution.config.crazyMode.comment: I wouldn't use this if I were you... Might have some strange effects.
evolution.config.drink.comment: The volume unit used by drinks in the game.
evolution.config.ecliptic.comment: Shows a green line in the skies representing the Ecliptic (the plane of the orbit of the Earth around the Sun).
evolution.config.firstPersonRenderer.com: Renders your body in first person as you would see it from your own eyes. Disabling is not supported and visual glitches may happen.
evolution.config.food.comment: The energy unit used by food in the game.
evolution.config.hitmarkers.comment: Shows hitmarkers when you damage or kill enemies.
evolution.config.limitTimeUnitsToHour.co: Limits the time units in the statistics screen to hours, instead of days and years.
evolution.config.mass.comment: The mass unit used in the game.
evolution.config.planets.comment:
Show outlines around the planets in the sky to better identify them.
Red is Mercury.
Orange is Venus.
Yellow is Mars.
Green is Jupiter.
Blue is Saturn.
evolution.config.showPlanets.comment: Shows the planets in the skies. Although immersive and realistic, they do not have any gameplay impact. Disabling them might slightly improve performance.
evolution.config.torchTime.comment:
Define the time in game hours the torch will be lit for.
0 will disable unliting.
evolution.config.volume.comment: The volume unit used in the game.
forge.configgui.alwaysSetupTerrainOffThr: May increase FPS significantly, but may also cause weird rendering lag. Not recommended for computers without a significant number of cores available.
forge.configgui.defaultWorldType.comment:
Defines a default world type to use. The vanilla default world type is represented by 'default'.
The modded world types are registry names which should include the registry namespace, such as 'examplemod:example_world_type'.
forge.configgui.fixAdvancementLoading.co: Fix advancement loading to use a proper topological sort. This may have visibility side-effects and can thus be turned off if needed for data-pack compatibility.
forge.configgui.forceSystemNanoTime.comm: Force the use of System.nanoTime instead of glfwGetTime as the main client time provider.
forge.configgui.forgeLightPipelineEnable: EXPERIMENTAL: Enable the forge block rendering pipeline - fixes the lighting of custom models.
forge.configgui.fullBoundingBoxLadders.c: Set this to true to check the entire entity's collision bounding box for ladders instead of just the block they are in. Causes noticeable differences in mechanics so default is vanilla behavior.
forge.configgui.removeErroringBlockEntit: Set this to true to remove any BlockEntity that throws an error in its update method instead of closing the server and reporting a crash log. BE WARNED THIS COULD SCREW UP EVERYTHING. USE SPARINGLY. WE ARE NOT RESPONSIBLE FOR DAMAGES.
forge.configgui.showLoadWarnings.comment: When enabled, Forge will show any warnings that occurred during loading.
forge.configgui.treatEmptyTagsAsAir.comm: Vanilla will treat crafting recipes using empty tags as air, and allow you to craft with nothing in that slot. This changes empty tags to use BARRIER as the item. To prevent crafting with air.
forge.configgui.useCombinedDepthStencilA: Set to true to use a combined DEPTH_STENCIL attachment instead of two separate ones.
forge.configgui.zombieBabyChance.comment: Chance that a zombie (or subclass) is a baby. Allows changing the zombie spawning mechanic.
forge.configgui.zombieBaseSummonChance.c: Base zombie summoning spawn chance. Allows changing the bonus zombie summoning mechanic.
